BACKGROUND: Both dental caries and periodontal disease, as isolated conditions, 
can generate limitations and disabilities with negative repercussions on the 
individual's quality of life, but the combination of both oral diseases has not 
been investigated yet. This study aimed to evaluate the association between the 
combined exposure to dental caries and periodontitis and the impact on oral 
health-related quality of life.
METHODS: A cross-sectional study was conducted among 306 individuals seen in the 
public health services in Feira de Santana, Bahia, Brazil. The individuals were 
divided into three groups: individuals without caries and periodontitis 
(n = 60), those with caries or periodontitis separately (n = 155), and those 
with both caries and periodontitis (n = 91). Information regarding 
sociodemographic, health conditions, behavioral aspects, and health-care 
characteristics were obtained through structured questionnaires. Oral clinical 
